each()

  each<T>(this, fn): Cheerio<T>

Defined in: src/api/traversing.ts:640

Iterates over a cheerio object, executing a function for each matched element. When the callback is
fired, the function is fired in the context of the DOM element, so this refers to the current element,
which is equivalent to the function parameter element. To break out of the each loop early, return with
false.

Type Parameters

• T

Parameters

this

Cheerio<T>

fn

(this, i, el) => boolean | void

Function to execute.

Returns

Cheerio<T>

The instance itself, useful for chaining.

Example

    const fruits = [];

    $('li').each(function (i, elem) {
      fruits[i] = $(this).text();
    });

    fruits.join(', ');
    //=> Apple, Orange, Pear

[][]

See

https://api.jquery.com/each/

