Function: load()

  load(content, options?, isDocument?): CheerioAPI

Defined in: src/load-parse.ts:31

Create a querying function, bound to a document created from the provided markup.

Note that similar to web browser contexts, this operation may introduce <html>, <head>, and <body>
elements; set isDocument to false to switch to fragment mode and disable this.

Parameters

content

Markup to be loaded.

string | AnyNode | AnyNode[] | Buffer

options?

Options for the created instance.

null | CheerioOptions

isDocument?

boolean

Allows parser to be switched to fragment mode.

Returns

CheerioAPI

The loaded document.

See

https://cheerio.js.org/docs/basics/loading#load for additional usage information.

